race.comment: NEXTONIXS (3) is a promising galloper resuming. Was a beaten favourite before a spell suggesting an issue but loves this course and distance and goes very well fresh. Has upside and worth following up. MINTULEE (2) is also worth forgiving last start. Was well off best figures last time in what has been a hot form race and has a great record this circuit including three wins. Drops in weight with the claim and can bounce back. GOLD SPIRIT (5) wasn't beaten far fresh here when fourth and will strip fitter. Has the claim and among the main hopes. BEEN OUR ANGEL (1) drew off the track here last time and burnt early before fading late. Much better draw so might have a little more gas late. IN LOVE (9) also led and was run down last time. Drops in weight with the same claimer and can give a sight at odds.
